<section class="section" id="projects" data-id="#03 / projekte">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="left">
        <span class="eyebrow">03 — Projekte</span>
        <h2>Was ich <em>so bau</em> &amp; betreibe.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="right">Discord-Bots · Automation · Web</div>
    </div>

    <div class="project-group">
      <div class="project-group-label"><span>Discord &amp; Gaming</span></div>
      <div class="project-grid">
        <div class="project-card flagship">
          <div class="project-card-head">
            <div class="project-card-title">aion2-guild-bot</div>
            <div class="project-badges">
              <span class="badge badge-pypi">Live</span>
              <span class="badge">Selbst gehostet</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="project-card-desc">Produktionsreifer Discord-Bot fürs Gilden-Management in Aion 2: Events &amp; Raids, DKP/EPGP/Loot-Council, Voice-Auto-Attendance, wiederkehrende Termine, CSV-Roster-Import.</p>
          <div class="project-stack">TypeScript · discord.js · PostgreSQL/Drizzle · 25 Slash-Commands · 325 Tests · Docker/VPS</div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <div class="project-card-head">
            <div class="project-card-title">aion2-dashboard</div>
            <div class="project-badges">
              <span class="badge">Prototyp</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="project-card-desc">Read-only Leiter-Dashboard für den Bot — Discord-OAuth nur für Identität, dünne Brille auf dieselbe Logik, on-demand hinter SSH-Tunnel statt Dauerdienst.</p>
          <div class="project-stack">Node · node:http · Discord-OAuth · Caddy</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="project-group">
      <div class="project-group-label"><span>Web &amp; Automation</span></div>
      <div class="project-grid">
        <div class="project-card flagship">
          <div class="project-card-head">
            <div class="project-card-title">ki-news</div>
            <div class="project-badges">
              <span class="badge badge-pypi">Live</span>
              <a href="https://news.reichenberg.ruhr" class="badge" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Newsletter</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="project-card-desc">Täglicher KI-News-Newsletter, vollautomatisch: headless-Recherche schreibt die Ausgabe, rendert sie ins HTML-Template und versendet sie als Kampagne — jeden Morgen per Cron.</p>
          <div class="project-stack">Bash · Claude headless · listmonk · täglich 06:20 Uhr</div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <div class="project-card-head">
            <div class="project-card-title">tiktok-poster</div>
            <div class="project-badges">
              <span class="badge">In Review</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="project-card-desc">Postet die Top-5-KI-GitHub-Repos der Woche als Foto-Carousel im Terminal-Look auf TikTok. App-Review bei TikTok eingereicht.</p>
          <div class="project-stack">Python · TikTok Content Posting API · Pillow</div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <div class="project-card-head">
            <div class="project-card-title">reichenberg.ruhr</div>
            <div class="project-badges">
              <span class="badge badge-pypi">Open Source</span>
              <a href="https://github.com/dennisreichenberg/reichenberg-ruhr" class="badge" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="project-card-desc">Diese Seite: statisch, Terminal-Ästhetik, eingebettete CLI und Vim-Navigation. Bewusst minimaler Dependency-Footprint, deployt über GitHub Pages.</p>
          <div class="project-stack">Astro · Vanilla JS/CSS · GitHub Pages</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .project-stack {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--muted);
